API Testing Standards:

Test Structure:
- Arrange: Prepare request payload
- Act: Call bridge endpoint
- Assert: Validate response

Validation Rules:
- Always validate:
  - HTTP status code
  - Response schema
  - Business logic fields
- Avoid partial assertions

Data Handling:
- Use dynamic data for zones and records
- Ensure uniqueness (e.g., timestamps in zone names)
- Avoid collisions across test runs

Negative Testing:
- Include scenarios for:
  - Non-existent zone retrieval
  - Invalid record types
  - Deleting already deleted zones
- Validate null/boolean responses correctly

Idempotency:
- Tests must be safe to re-run
- Ensure cleanup:
  - Delete created zones after test execution

Logging Validation:
- Ensure requests are logged in powerdns_api.log
- Validate presence of:
  - method
  - URL
  - payload
  - response code

Do NOT:
- Hardcode assertions without verifying actual API behavior
- Skip validation of edge cases